Yeah was adding a debug target to the Dockerfile, yet to interact with VSCode, it requires to have an extension installed (Dev containers (https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=ms-vscode-remote.remote-containers)) that I do not see in marketplace for the web IDE. Then would need a `launch.json` debugging config like:
```{
  "version": "0.2.0",
  "configurations": [
    {
      "name": "Python: Remote Attach",
      "type": "python",
      "request": "attach",
      "connect": {
        "host": "localhost",
        "port": 5678
      },
      "pathMappings": [
        {
          "localRoot": "${workspaceFolder}", // Local project directory
          "remoteRoot": "/model-service/py"   // Directory inside the container
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}```
; yet will give `epd`  first a try :wink:
